logbook.docsRmk: Forgot to descend shortly before final so I needed to fly an extra round. Speed management needed to much work due to first time experience. 180 kt could not be flown cleanly so correct flap settings needed to be determined and executed. Should have initiated the descent prior to this.

logbook.docsRmk: Forgot to start FSUIPC prior to start so STKP couldn't record. Restarted the flight, don't forget again. Also check descend levels twice, TOD could have been later and do the same with speed restrictions. If a point between to restrictions has no restriction set the plane will automatically accelerate. Just set the speed.

logbook.docsRmk: First NDB VOR DME Approach including maximum crosswind on an airport that is not build for an A320 Neo... noice

logbook.route: EGPO/18 H6105 EKVG/30
logbook.docsRmk: Horrible descend, could have been a lot later, don't actually know what happened, wind maybe? There was a strong side wind from the left with a slight tailwind component. Wind speed of around 80-90 knots. Landing happened with 40 knots wind from oppsing side with gusts at around 1000 feet. Landing felt like slow motion, very interesting but in the end I underestimated the side vector of the wind and was blown a bit of center line.

logbook.route: EKVG/30 MY2N MY LARUX BAULA BIEG/03
logbook.docsRmk: Horrible descend again, forget the strong headwind and descend a lot quicker, so I needed to ascend again to avoid terrain.

logbook.route: BIEG/03 FELI1B FELLI BRUSI ASKJA DEVUD ABEXI DEXON KFI01 SUVIL BIKF/28
logbook.docsRmk: Better descend in 110 knots headwind, but still there must be a formula for this. I used VS mode in combination with Open Descend and cross checked every 5 miles the calculator with the actual DME to adjust the rate. Landing was in very bad visibility, airport came into sight about 100 feet above minimum.
